    "We use the ULTRANEST nested sampling algorithm (Buchner 2016(Buchner, 2019(Buchner, 2021)) to perform Bayesian inference on the likelihood of Eq.",
    "( 4) and determine posteriors for the various model parameters.",
    "For this exercise we parameterise the positional uncertainties of individual sources asσ i = POS_ERR = A • σ 2 + σ 2 0,(5)where σ = RADEC_ERR/ √ 2 and RADEC_ERR is the catalogued positional uncertainty produced by ermldet (see Eq.",
    "( 5) above, σ 0 represents systematic uncertainties and A is a multiplicative factor that scales the ermldet uncertainties.",
    "Under these assumptions, the four model parameters that are inferred by modelling the distribution of Fig. 14 are ρ, F, A, σ 0."
